sub_title: Master student Civil Engineering and Management | Teaching Assistant Newtonian Mechanics
summary: I am a passionate PhD-candidate in the Marine and Fluvial Systems group at the University of Twente, where I research the effect of sand extractions on the sea bed, and specifically the interaction between the sea bed and benthic life. I'm focussing on modelling this system by means of complex numerical and idealised models, hence I'm not scared of a bit of math!
